ScoreAccessLog - Class in com.energyxxer.commodore.functionlogic.score.access
Structure which stores all the scoreboard accesses of all the entries of a Function, and gives each of them a resolution based on their order: Used and Unused.
Used: This means that the scoreboard access is either of type Read, or that it is of type Write, and succeeded by another of type Read that accesses the same macro score holder. Unused: This means that the scoreboard access is unused or redundant.
ScoreAccessLog(Function) - Constructor for class com.energyxxer.commodore.functionlogic.score.access.ScoreAccessLog
Creates a score access log for the given function.
